      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this way; it sounds like an incredibly heavy and overwhelming time for you. Please know that your feelings are valid, and reaching out is a brave first step. While I cannot take the pressure away right now, I can offer some gentle support and resources to help you find relief.\n\nIf you are in immediate distress or feel like you might harm yourself, please reach out to a crisis line right away. In the US, you can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, which offers 24/7 free and confidential support. If you are outside the US, please look for local emergency services or a crisis helpline in your country. You don't have to carry this alone.\n\nEven though the world feels like it's closing in, there are people who want to listen and help you navigate through this storm. Sometimes, just talking to a trusted friend, family member, or a mental health professional can make a huge difference. You are stronger than this, even if it doesn't feel like it right now. Please consider reaching out to someone who can offer you a safe space to breathe.",
