    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and I want to acknowledge that the exhaustion of trying to \"fix\" things when everything feels broken is a incredibly heavy burden to carry. It makes perfect sense that you feel like your efforts are backfiring; when you are drowning, every extra splash just feels like more pressure. The feeling that it's endless and that fighting is futile is a very real and painful experience, and it's okay to feel that way right now.\n\nHowever, I also want to gently remind you that while the pain feels absolute, it is not permanent, even if it feels that way in the moment. Sometimes, the most powerful thing you can do is not to fight the wave, but to let someone else hold the rope for you while you rest. You don't have to solve the whole mess today; you just have to get through the next hour, or the next day.\n\nIf you are feeling like you can't go on, please consider reaching out to a crisis line one more time, even if it feels like a waste of time. They are trained to sit with you in the dark without trying to \"fix\" anything immediately, just to listen. You deserve to be heard, and you deserve support, even when you don",
